     1|/**
     2| * IVX Admin Sync — owner-only, one-shot delivery chain:
     3| *
     4| *   Rork workspace → GitHub push → Render deploy → live /health verification
     5| *
     6| *   POST /api/ivx/admin/sync-rork-to-github
     7| *
     8| * Runs the existing `expo/sync-github.mjs` push server-side using the backend's
     9| * own GITHUB_TOKEN / GITHUB_REPO_URL (branch GITHUB_BRANCH || main), re-reads the
    10| * branch ref to confirm the pushed HEAD SHA, triggers a Render deploy via
    11| * RENDER_API_KEY / RENDER_SERVICE_ID, then polls the live /health endpoint
    12| * (PRODUCTION_BASE_URL) and compares its reported commit SHA to GitHub HEAD.
    13| *
    14| * No credentials are accepted from the request body and none are ever returned;
    15| * any incidental secret occurrence in script output is redacted.
    16| *
    17| * Returns the owner's exact field set:
    18| *   SYNC_HTTP_STATUS, GITHUB_PUSHED, GITHUB_HEAD_SHA, GITHUB_COMMIT_URL,
    19| *   RENDER_DEPLOY_TRIGGERED, RENDER_DEPLOY_ID, RENDER_STATUS,
    20| *   HEALTH_HTTP_STATUS, PRODUCTION_HEALTH_SHA, MATCH_GITHUB_TO_HEALTH, FINAL_STATUS
    21| * On failure additionally:
    22| *   FAILED_AT, RAW_ERROR, MISSING_ENV, NEXT_OWNER_ACTION
    23| */
